1
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:06,440
Got it.

2
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:07,640
Over here.

3
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:18,920
I'll bet on three months.

4
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,120
High odds. I'll take a chance.

5
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,579
Three months pays triple.

6
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,920
One month is a sure thing.

7
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:23,840
Think about it.

8
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,140
Come take a look. Place your bets.

9
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,600
One month is a sure thing.

10
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,760
Sanxi,

11
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,570
what are they doing?

12
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,880
These men are so boring.

13
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,440
They're placing bets.

14
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:44,800
They say Lin Lan won't last a week

15
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,720
before her uncle drives her away.

16
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:49,280
.

17
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,320
He's quick-witted

18
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,280
and agile.

19
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,040
But he's

20
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,040
a bit too rigid.

21
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,970
But with some training,

22
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,500
he should improve.

23
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:18,600
Dr. Qin.

24
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,370
What's your bet?

25
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,800
Bet on one month.

26
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,800
One month is a safe bet.

27
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,840
It's easy money.

28
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:24,920
Trust me.

29
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,520
Stop.

30
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:29,520
If we're betting, let's make it exciting.

31
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,380
What about you?

32
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,680
Get your money ready.

33
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,920
Don't be sore losers.

34
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,840
Who do you think we are?

35
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,730
Bet on this. The one-month option.

36
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,560
I bet one year.

37
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,210
I'll collect from you this time next year.

38
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,360
A bet is a bet.

39
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,280
Don't be a sore loser then.

40
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,040
Come on, let's continue.

41
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,200
Ignore her. Let's go on.

42
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,040
She dares to bet one year.

43
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,440
Anyone for three months?

44
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,180
She really dares to bet a year.

45
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:03,880
Miss Lin,

46
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,050
are you experimenting this early?

47
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:09,560
No.

48
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,280
You clearly wrote "Mouthwash Only".

49
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,920
Why is it liquor?

50
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,740
I use it to rinse and disinfect after autopsies.

51
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,000
Smile. Let me see.

52
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,130
Did you brush your teeth with this?

53
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,680
Yes.

54
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,760
It's shoe polish.

55
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,480
Why did you put shoe polish here?

56
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,760
It's Bao's.

57
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,159
But it's clearly white,

58
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,520
and smells like mint.

59
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,880
Don't you know color-changing shoe polish?

60
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,409
You came back from France and don't know that?

61
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,340
France doesn't have this either.

62
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:53,200
Tongtong.

63
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,200
Tongtong.

64
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:56,800
Tongtong.

65
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:57,600
Mom, look.

66
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:55,800
Qin Xin.

67
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,720
You know Shanghai well.

68
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,720
Help me find a place.

69
00:05:58,720 --> 00:05:59,320
Be quiet.

70
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:07,680
You're leaving the grand Lin Mansion behind

71
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:09,640
just to live on your own.

72
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,920
The monthly utilities cost a lot.

73
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,410
Don't worry about that.

74
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,680
I just want somewhere quiet.

75
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,520
It doesn't have to be big.

76
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,290
Fair enough.

77
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,200
Moving out

78
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,300
makes investigating easier.

79
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,160
Lin Lan.

80
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:35,000
I think you're cut out to be an inspector.

81
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,400
No matter how hard the case gets,

82
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,240
don't give up, okay?

83
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,360
Is your head still not right?

84
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,890
Why say that all of a sudden?

85
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:46,159
You're just like your grandfather.

86
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,600
I'm hungry. Buy me a meal.

87
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:51,520
Wait.

88
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,200
Why should I buy you a meal?

89
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,600
I told you not to come, yet here you are.

90
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,720
Why are you stopping me?

91
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,560
I want to report a case.

92
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,560
How many times have I said it?

93
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,840
Your case is closed.

94
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,720
Don't stop me.

95
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,680
I want to report a case.

96
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,280
Your case is already closed.

97
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:05,280
What's the use of coming here now, Officer?

98
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,080
Officer, I want to report a case.

99
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,680
Why won't you let me in?

100
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,360
What's going on?

101
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,360
What's all the fuss about?

102
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:11,960
I want to report a case.

103
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:12,760
It's already closed.

104
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:13,820
What's happening?

105
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,680
Inspector.

106
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,540
Inspector Lin.

107
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:16,640
I want to report a case.

108
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,120
My child is missing, Inspector.

109
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,640
Her case was closed a long time ago.

110
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,880
The kidnappers were executed. Get up first.

111
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:21,960
It's not closed.

112
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,450
I am the child's mother.

113
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,880
Believe me. I can sense it.

114
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,880
My child is waiting for me to save her, Inspector.

115
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,880
Get up first.

116
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,840
Let's talk slowly, okay?

117
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,280
Inspector.

118
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:32,520
Come here.

119
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,720
I want to show you something.

120
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,280
Okay.

121
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,120
Look.

122
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,900
This is from back then.

123
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,440
The crime scene where my child was taken.

124
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:39,440
I drew it all.

125
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,680
I was right here in this alley.

126
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,159
Lin Lan.

127
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:41,760
I found a pool of blood.

128
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,400
Lin Lan, wait a moment.

129
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,760
And on top of the blood...

130
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,490
Wait. I have serious business.

131
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,600
Something happened at the market.

132
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,659
A child is missing.

133
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,940
A pool of blood was found at the scene.

134
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,320
I'll get the investigation kit.

135
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:53,640
Go.

136
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:54,640
Wait.

137
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,520
Who drew this?

138
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,200
That's exactly what the scene looks like.

139
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,860
A shoe on top of a pool of blood.

140
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,480
Back up.

141
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,000
Move.

142
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,960
Step back.

143
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:11,760
Back up.

144
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:13,650
Nothing to see here.

145
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,300
Don't push. Step back.

146
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,460
Everyone, back up.

147
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,000
When did you two

148
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,730
realize the child was missing?

149
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,960
I was buying something,

150
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,540
and when I turned around, he was gone.

151
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,600
Yunpian cakes! Take a look!

152
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,680
How much for these?

153
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,560
Five wen for one.

154
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,360
I'll take one.

155
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,039
Sure thing.

156
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,400
Here you go.

157
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,080
Okay.

158
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,840
Here is the money.

159
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,000
Thanks.

160
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:42,740
Where is Tongtong?

161
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,600
Tongtong?

162
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,120
Tongtong!

163
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,920
Tongtong!

164
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,560
Tongtong!

165
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,440
It's all my fault.

166
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,200
If I hadn't stopped to buy things,

167
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,330
Tongtong wouldn't have disappeared.

168
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,600
Don't cry.

169
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,170
It's not your fault.

170
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,500
Tongtong will be fine.

171
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,700
Let's not think the worst.

172
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,120
So much blood.

173
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,680
Tongtong is most afraid of blood.

174
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,120
Where could he have gone?

175
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,920
Calm down first.

176
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:16,960
Do you remember what the child was wearing?

177
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,940
He was wearing a light brown Mandarin jacket

178
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,580
and a skullcap on his head.

179
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,600
Does the child have any other distinguishing features,

180
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,730
like something easily recognizable?

181
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:30,520
He was wearing yellowish-brown trousers.

182
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,600
The legs were a bit short,

183
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:35,120
so I sewed a strip of black hem on them.

184
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:36,880
Do you two usually

185
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,040
have any enemies?

186
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:40,170
Or have you offended anyone recently?

187
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,680
We just sell wontons.

188
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,680
We haven't offended anyone.

189
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,360
We understand the situation.

190
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,620
Please go back for now.

191
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,720
If there are any developments,

192
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,850
we will contact you.

193
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,600
If you remember anything,

194
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,400
please let us know immediately.

195
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,080
Thank you, Inspector.

196
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,760
Thank you.

197
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,120
I asked around.

198
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,520
No one noticed anyone taking the child.

199
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,640
After a precipitation test,

200
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,900
the blood at the scene isn't human blood.

201
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,800
I tried matching it

202
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,060
with several common animal blood types.

203
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,780
It's pigeon blood.

204
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:24,120
That means Gu Yitong

205
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:24,920
might not be dead

206
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:26,520
but was taken by kidnappers.

207
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:29,160
But couldn't the kidnappers just take the child?

208
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,720
Why create a pool of pigeon blood

209
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,850
just to play tricks?

210
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,120
A few years ago, a kidnapping ring

211
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,650
used the exact same method.

212
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,120
They left blood at the scene

213
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,320
to mislead us.

214
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,520
Where is the woman who reported the case this morning?

215
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,240
She hasn't left yet.

216
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,970
She said she's waiting for you.

217
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:49,680
Officer.

218
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,040
That gang is back, isn't it?

219
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,560
They are the kidnappers

220
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:55,290
who took my daughter back then.

221
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:57,050
We understand how you feel,

222
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,200
but right now,

223
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,800
there is no evidence to prove

224
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,200
that it's the same group.

225
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,040
That officer just said

226
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,480
the modus operandi is the same as back then.

227
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,640
It's the same group.

228
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,760
I'm sure of it.

229
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:12,860
Have a seat.

230
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,400
Can you tell us in detail

231
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:20,000
what happened the day your child went missing?

232
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,520
Eight years ago.

233
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:25,800
That day,

234
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,960
I was in a rush to deliver clothes to my employer.

235
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,760
It'll take less than 20 minutes.

236
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,560
Coax her a bit.

237
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,480
Don't let her keep crying.

238
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,840
I'll deliver Mrs. Luo's clothes

239
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,840
and be right back.

240
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:45,640
Watch her closely. Don't fall asleep.

241
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:46,370
Don't worry.

242
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,400
Be a good girl, Shengnan.

243
00:11:58,800 --> 00:11:59,860
Where is Shengnan?

244
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:01,720
Shengnan!

245
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:03,760
Shengnan!

246
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:06,840
Get up!

247
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,840
Where is Shengnan?

248
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,720
Didn't I tell you not to sleep?

249
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,840
She was just here.

250
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:12,720
Why are you just standing there?

251
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,960
Go find her!

252
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:15,720
Shengnan!

253
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,840
Shengnan!

254
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,720
Shengnan!

255
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,480
Shengnan's shoe.

256
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:44,120
Has anyone seen Shengnan?

257
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,660
How are you sure the child is still alive?

258
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,720
The blood on this isn't human blood.

259
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,240
I had it tested.

260
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:53,740
It's pigeon blood.

261
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:55,160
Sir.

262
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:57,320
It's actually a diversion.

263
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,640
They used this blood

264
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:01,140
to make us think the child was killed.

265
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,800
But actually, she was sold by traffickers.

266
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,960
The gang even gave themselves a name:

267
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,240
Ghost Mother.

268
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:09,600
Sounds mysterious.

269
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,200
Actually, the women steal,

270
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,280
and the men sell.

271
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,280
The men are the "Ghosts,"

272
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,880
and the women are the "Mothers."

273
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:15,680
Back then,

274
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,080
many children were stolen this way.

275
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:19,200
Later on,

276
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,440
as you know,

277
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:22,080
the gang was caught.

278
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,240
The female kidnappers were all executed.

279
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,320
But the case was never closed.

280
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:27,840
You mean

281
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,240
the male traffickers are still active?

282
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:33,040
None of the men were caught.

283
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:35,160
Now they're striking again.

284
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,120
Sir,

285
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:36,840
if we find him,

286
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,160
we'll find my daughter.

287
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,840
He must know where she is.

288
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,480
Is the Ghost Mother gang

289
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,920
really active again?

290
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,240
What Ghost Mother?

291
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:53,700
They are just kidnappers.

